    // ─── Phase 4.1 — chronic stubs (scars) ─────────────────────────────
    // recoveryMode: 'chronic-permanent' — the phase machine fast-paths
    // these to peak on day-1 and holds them at the authored severity
    // forever. They never resolve, never recover, never re-scar. Each
    // chronic stub is the souvenir of a severe acute/injury bout.
    //
    // Templates are body-part-scoped — a scar lives where the wound
    // happened. The bands carry permanent stat penalties (Endurance cap
    // for scarred-lung, walkingSpeed for weak-joint, etc.) — small but
    // visible numbers, so the player feels every survived disaster.
    //
    // No bands are emitted while severity < the lowest band lo; chronic
    // stubs author their permanent severity above [20, ...] so the band
    // is always-on once the stub reaches peak.

